  <title>MANAGER – GRANTS (2-YEAR CONTRACT)</title>
  <link>https://www.ub.bw/connect/job-opportunities/manager-%E2%80%93-grants-2-year-contract</link>
  <description>&lt;span class="field field--name-title field--type-string field--label-hidden"&gt;MANAGER – GRANTS (2-YEAR CONTRACT)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="field field--name-uid field--type-entity-reference field--label-hidden"&gt;&lt;a title="View user profile." href="https://www.ub.bw/user/1558" lang="" about="https://www.ub.bw/user/1558" typeof="schema:Person" property="schema:name" datatype="" class="username" xml:lang=""&gt;ramahobok&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="field field--name-created field--type-created field--label-hidden"&gt;Wed, 08/03/2023 - 11:28&lt;/span&gt;

  &lt;div class="field field--name-field-department field--type-entity-reference field--label-inline clearfix"&gt;
    &lt;div class="field__label"&gt;Department/Faculty&lt;/div&gt;
              &lt;div class="field__item"&gt;Faculty of Medicine&lt;/div&gt;
          &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;div class="field field--name-field-tender-closing-date field--type-datetime field--label-inline clearfix"&gt;
    &lt;div class="field__label"&gt;Closing Date&lt;/div&gt;
              &lt;div class="field__item"&gt;Wed, 22 Mar. 2023&lt;/div&gt;
          &lt;/div&gt;

            &lt;div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field__item"&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;FACULTY OF MEDICINE&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;RESEARCH AND GRADUATE STUDIES&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;MANAGER – GRANTS (2-YEAR CONTRACT)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;VACANCY NO: FM/RGS01/2023&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Duties:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; the successful candidate will be expected to: &lt;strong&gt;i)&lt;/strong&gt; provide senior-level oversight of grants management of various internally and externally funded consultancies, projects and studies undertaken in the Faculty of Medicine; &lt;strong&gt;ii)&lt;/strong&gt; coordinate and support grant implementation processes, throughout the grants life cycle, as required; &lt;a&gt; &lt;strong&gt;iii)&lt;/strong&gt; supervise research office administrative support staff; and&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt;iv)&lt;/strong&gt; provide compliance-oriented, grants management guidance to department level support staff involved with grant implementation. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;This post will report to the Deputy Dean, Research and Graduate Studies, Faculty of Medicine, University of Botswana. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Specific Responsibilities:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;strong&gt;i) &lt;/strong&gt;ensure that there is compliance to funding agency rules and regulations; &lt;strong&gt;ii) &lt;/strong&gt;demonstrate understanding of funding agency rules in the management of funded projects; &lt;strong&gt;iii) &lt;/strong&gt;prepare and/or review budgets for proposed or existing projects; &lt;strong&gt;iv) &lt;/strong&gt;contribute to and lead in grant preparation (especially budget and budget justification); &lt;strong&gt;v)&lt;/strong&gt; predict expenditure and provide principal investigator(s) with forecasts; &lt;strong&gt;vi) &lt;/strong&gt; monitor grant budget spending to ensure appropriate spend rate; &lt;strong&gt;vii) &lt;/strong&gt;prepare reports as required by funding agencies and internal stakeholders; &lt;strong&gt;viii) &lt;/strong&gt;facilitate and participate in required funding agency reporting; &lt;strong&gt;ix) &lt;/strong&gt;prioritise work based on deadlines, including working with sub-awardees (if University of Botswana is prime) or Prime (if University of Botswana is a sub-awardee); &lt;strong&gt;x) &lt;/strong&gt;supervise and mentor research office support staff; &lt;strong&gt;xi) &lt;/strong&gt;carry out other duties and responsibilities as assigned.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Requirements: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;strong&gt;i) &lt;/strong&gt;first degree in &lt;a&gt;Finance or equivalent&lt;/a&gt;; &lt;strong&gt;ii) &lt;/strong&gt;at least 5 years experience coordinating business processes of research, including pre-award and post-award, and engagement with funders and other stakeholders; &lt;strong&gt;iii)&lt;/strong&gt; at least 2 years experience as a supervisor. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Attributes and skills required: i) &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;budgeting and accounting experience skills;&lt;strong&gt; ii) &lt;/strong&gt;excellent communication and organisational skills;&lt;strong&gt; iii) &lt;/strong&gt;strong leadership qualities, sound analytical and coordinating skills; &lt;strong&gt;iv) &lt;/strong&gt;ability to work and collaborate well with team members from multiple&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;disciplines and multiple institutions;&lt;strong&gt; v) &lt;/strong&gt;knowledge of donor agencies;&lt;strong&gt; vi) &lt;/strong&gt;strong English writing skills and use of Excel.  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Remuneration:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; the University offers competitive salaries and benefits commensurate with experience and qualifications.  For more information on the University, please visit our website; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.ub.bw"&gt;&lt;span&gt;www.ub.bw&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;How to apply:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; applicants should address the stated qualifications and provide any other information to assist the University determine their suitability for the position.  They should quote the vacancy number of the post applied for, provide current CVs (including telephone, skype and email address), certified true copies of educational certificates, transcripts, names, addresses and contact details of three referees. &lt;strong&gt;Applicants should inform their referees to:&lt;/strong&gt;  &lt;strong&gt;(i)&lt;/strong&gt; quote the vacancy number; &lt;strong&gt;(ii)&lt;/strong&gt; position applied for, and; &lt;strong&gt;(iii)&lt;/strong&gt; submit the references directly to the address stated below before the stipulated closing date:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Human Resources Manager, Faculty of Medicine, Corner of Notwane and Mabuto Road, University of Botswana, Private Bag 00713 Gaborone, Botswana; or Email &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;tshoganetsom@ub.ac.bw&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Hand delivered applications should be sent to:&lt;strong&gt; Faculty of Medicine, Sir Ketumile Masire Teaching Hospital (SKMTH), 3rd Floor, Office F4003 or F4004.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

